Title: [GPS Manager][Navigation]Verify that User can navigate to Dashboard successfully
Description: Navigate to Dashboard landing page to access GPS Manager functionality
Steps: 1. Open staging dashboard URL; 2. Wait for page loading completion; 3. Verify dashboard header appears; 4. Check navigation menu visibility; 5. Confirm main content area displays; 6. Verify sidebar elements load; 7. Validate all dashboard components are interactive
Expected Result: 1. Browser navigates to staging dashboard successfully; 2. Page loading indicators complete; 3. Dashboard header displays with correct branding; 4. Navigation menu items are visible and accessible; 5. Main content area shows dashboard elements; 6. Sidebar navigation loads properly; 7. All dashboard components are fully functional and responsive

Title: [GPS Manager][Module Access]Verify that User can access GPS Data Analytics module successfully
Description: Open GPS Data Analytics module from menu
Steps: 1. Locate Gps Data Analytics in navigation menu; 2. Click on Gps Data Analytics menu item; 3. Wait for module loading process; 4. Verify GPS Analytics page initialization; 5. Check page title and header elements; 6. Confirm navigation controls appear; 7. Validate all GPS Analytics features are accessible
Expected Result: 1. Gps Data Analytics menu item is visible and highlighted; 2. Menu click triggers navigation to GPS Analytics; 3. Loading process initiates with visual indicators; 4. GPS Analytics page loads completely; 5. Page displays correct title and header information; 6. Navigation controls for GPS Analytics are functional; 7. All GPS Analytics dashboard features are available

Title: [GPS Manager][Date Filter]Verify that User can filter playback by date range successfully
Description: Filter playback data using specific date range
Steps: 1. Locate date range selector control; 2. Click on start date input field; 3. Enter start date 2025-01-01; 4. Click on end date input field; 5. Enter end date 2025-01-03; 6. Click apply or confirm filter button; 7. Wait for filtered data to load and verify results
Expected Result: 1. Date range selector is visible and accessible; 2. Start date field becomes active for input; 3. Start date 2025-01-01 is entered and validated; 4. End date field becomes active for input; 5. End date 2025-01-03 is entered and validated; 6. Filter application triggers data processing; 7. Data reloads showing only selected period with loading confirmation

Title: [GPS Manager][Vehicle Search]Verify that User can search multiple vehicles successfully
Description: Search for specific vehicles by their identifiers
Precondition: GPS data must exist for selected date
Steps: 1. Locate vehicle search input field; 2. Enter CAO 8070 in search field; 3. Press enter or click search button; 4. Verify CAO 8070 results appear; 5. Enter WJ 3500 in search field; 6. Press enter or click search button; 7. Confirm both vehicles are listed in results
Expected Result: 1. Vehicle search field is visible and accessible; 2. CAO 8070 is entered correctly in search field; 3. Search action is triggered for CAO 8070; 4. CAO 8070 search results display with vehicle information; 5. WJ 3500 is entered correctly in search field; 6. Search action is triggered for WJ 3500; 7. Both vehicles CAO 8070 and WJ 3500 are listed with complete data

Title: [GPS Manager][Vehicle Selection]Verify that User can select multiple vehicle checkboxes successfully
Description: Select both searched vehicles using checkboxes
Steps: 1. Locate checkbox for CAO 8070 in results; 2. Click on CAO 8070 checkbox; 3. Verify checkbox state changes to selected; 4. Locate checkbox for WJ 3500 in results; 5. Click on WJ 3500 checkbox; 6. Observe map loading animation; 7. Verify both vehicles appear on map
Expected Result: 1. CAO 8070 checkbox is visible next to vehicle entry; 2. CAO 8070 checkbox changes to selected state; 3. Visual feedback confirms CAO 8070 selection; 4. WJ 3500 checkbox is visible next to vehicle entry; 5. WJ 3500 checkbox changes to selected state; 6. Loading animation appears on map area; 7. Map displays both vehicles with paths and location markers

Title: [GPS Manager][Map Interface]Verify that User can view vehicle chips under map successfully
Description: Verify selected vehicles appear as chips under map
Steps: 1. Locate chip area under map interface; 2. Verify CAO 8070 chip is displayed; 3. Check CAO 8070 chip information accuracy; 4. Verify WJ 3500 chip is displayed; 5. Check WJ 3500 chip information accuracy; 6. Confirm chips are interactive; 7. Validate chip styling and positioning
Expected Result: 1. Chip area is visible under map interface; 2. CAO 8070 chip appears with vehicle identifier; 3. CAO 8070 chip shows accurate vehicle information; 4. WJ 3500 chip appears with vehicle identifier; 5. WJ 3500 chip shows accurate vehicle information; 6. Both chips respond to hover and click interactions; 7. Chips are properly styled and positioned for optimal visibility

Title: [GPS Manager][Path Visualization]Verify that User can view different colored paths for vehicles successfully
Description: Validate that each vehicle displays unique path color
Steps: 1. Observe CAO 8070 vehicle path on map; 2. Note the color of CAO 8070 path; 3. Observe WJ 3500 vehicle path on map; 4. Note the color of WJ 3500 path; 5. Compare the two path colors; 6. Verify colors are distinctly different; 7. Confirm paths remain consistent during playback
Expected Result: 1. CAO 8070 vehicle path is visible on map; 2. CAO 8070 path displays in first distinct color; 3. WJ 3500 vehicle path is visible on map; 4. WJ 3500 path displays in second distinct color; 5. Path colors are clearly different from each other; 6. Colors are easily distinguishable for accessibility; 7. Path colors remain consistent throughout entire playback session

Title: [GPS Manager][Vehicle Management]Verify that User can unselect vehicle from sidebar successfully
Description: Remove vehicle selection from left panel
Steps: 1. Locate CAO 8070 in sidebar vehicle list; 2. Find the checkbox next to CAO 8070; 3. Click to uncheck CAO 8070 checkbox; 4. Observe immediate visual feedback; 5. Wait for map loading animation; 6. Verify CAO 8070 path removed from map; 7. Confirm CAO 8070 no longer appears in selected list
Expected Result: 1. CAO 8070 is visible in sidebar vehicle list; 2. Checkbox next to CAO 8070 is currently checked; 3. Checkbox changes to unchecked state when clicked; 4. Visual feedback shows deselection is processing; 5. Loading animation appears on map area; 6. CAO 8070 vehicle path disappears from map display; 7. CAO 8070 is removed from selected vehicles list

Title: [GPS Manager][Chip Management]Verify that User can remove vehicle using chip successfully
Description: Remove vehicle from map using chip close button
Steps: 1. Locate WJ 3500 chip under map; 2. Find the X close button on chip; 3. Click the X button on WJ 3500 chip; 4. Observe chip removal animation; 5. Wait for map update processing; 6. Verify WJ 3500 path removed from map; 7. Confirm WJ 3500 removed from vehicle list
Expected Result: 1. WJ 3500 chip is visible under map area; 2. X close button is clearly visible on chip; 3. X button click triggers removal action; 4. Chip removal animation plays smoothly; 5. Map processing indicator shows update in progress; 6. WJ 3500 vehicle path disappears from map completely; 7. WJ 3500 is removed from selected vehicles and chip area

Title: [GPS Manager][Playback Control]Verify that User can play timeline for multiple vehicles successfully
Description: Play animation timeline showing both vehicles simultaneously
Precondition: Map loaded with paths for both vehicles
Steps: 1. Locate playback control panel; 2. Click on play button; 3. Observe playback initialization; 4. Monitor CAO 8070 vehicle icon movement; 5. Monitor WJ 3500 vehicle icon movement; 6. Verify timeline progression; 7. Confirm simultaneous movement coordination
Expected Result: 1. Playback control panel is visible and accessible; 2. Play button click starts animation process; 3. Playback initialization begins for both vehicles; 4. CAO 8070 icon starts moving along its path; 5. WJ 3500 icon starts moving along its path; 6. Timeline progresses showing current position; 7. Both vehicles move simultaneously in coordinated fashion

Title: [GPS Manager][UI Interaction]Verify that User can focus on vehicle using chip selection successfully
Description: Select specific vehicle chip to focus view
Steps: 1. Locate CAO 8070 chip under map; 2. Click on CAO 8070 chip; 3. Observe chip visual state change; 4. Verify chip color changes to blue; 5. Check map focus changes; 6. Confirm only CAO 8070 icon visible; 7. Validate other vehicle icons are hidden
Expected Result: 1. CAO 8070 chip is visible and clickable; 2. Chip click triggers focus action; 3. Chip visual appearance changes immediately; 4. Chip background color changes to blue; 5. Map adjusts focus to CAO 8070 vehicle; 6. Only CAO 8070 vehicle icon remains visible on map; 7. Other vehicle icons are hidden while maintaining path visibility

Title: [GPS Manager][Dropdown Functions]Verify that User can access vehicle dropdown options successfully
Description: Check vehicle dropdown for additional options
Steps: 1. Locate WJ 3500 in sidebar vehicle list; 2. Find dropdown arrow or expand button; 3. Click to expand dropdown menu; 4. Verify dropdown opens completely; 5. Check for open route toggle option; 6. Check for job toggle option; 7. Confirm all dropdown options are accessible
Expected Result: 1. WJ 3500 is visible in sidebar vehicle list; 2. Dropdown expansion control is visible and accessible; 3. Dropdown menu opens when clicked; 4. Dropdown displays all available options; 5. Open route toggle option is visible and functional; 6. Job toggle option is visible and functional; 7. All dropdown options respond to interaction appropriately

Title: [GPS Manager][Route Display]Verify that User can enable open route toggle successfully
Description: Activate open route display for selected vehicle
Steps: 1. Access CAO 8070 dropdown in sidebar; 2. Locate open route toggle option; 3. Click to toggle ON open route; 4. Observe toggle state change; 5. Wait for map processing; 6. Verify open route appears on map; 7. Confirm route display is distinct from path
Expected Result: 1. CAO 8070 dropdown is accessible and expanded; 2. Open route toggle option is visible; 3. Toggle changes to ON state when clicked; 4. Toggle visual state confirms activation; 5. Map processing indicator shows route loading; 6. Open route is displayed on map for CAO 8070; 7. Route display is visually distinct from regular vehicle path

Title: [GPS Manager][Job Management]Verify that User can toggle job pagination successfully
Description: Enable job pagination to show vehicle loads
Steps: 1. Access WJ 3500 dropdown in sidebar; 2. Locate job pagination toggle; 3. Click to toggle ON job pagination; 4. Observe toggle state change; 5. Wait for job data loading; 6. Verify job loads appear in interface; 7. Confirm job pagination controls are functional
Expected Result: 1. WJ 3500 dropdown is accessible and expanded; 2. Job pagination toggle is visible and accessible; 3. Toggle changes to ON state when clicked; 4. Toggle visual feedback confirms activation; 5. Loading indicator shows job data being retrieved; 6. Job loads appear in vehicle interface section; 7. Pagination controls allow navigation through job loads

Title: [GPS Manager][Geofence Display]Verify that User can view job geofence on map successfully
Description: Select specific load to display job path and geofence
Precondition: Job toggle is ON for vehicle
Steps: 1. Locate job load checkbox for WJ 3500; 2. Click on specific job load checkbox; 3. Observe loading animation start; 4. Wait for job path processing; 5. Verify job path appears on map; 6. Confirm geofence boundaries display; 7. Validate geofence and path integration
Expected Result: 1. Job load checkbox is visible for WJ 3500; 2. Checkbox click triggers job load selection; 3. Loading animation appears on map area; 4. Job path processing completes successfully; 5. Job-specific path is rendered on map; 6. Geofence boundaries are clearly visible around job area; 7. Geofence and job path are properly integrated and distinguishable

Title: [GPS Manager][Route Toggle]Verify that User can display only open route successfully
Description: Toggle to show only job route without other paths
Steps: 1. Locate open route only toggle; 2. Check current toggle state; 3. Click to enable open route only mode; 4. Observe toggle state change; 5. Wait for map display update; 6. Verify only job route is visible; 7. Confirm other vehicle paths are hidden
Expected Result: 1. Open route only toggle is visible and accessible; 2. Current toggle state is clearly indicated; 3. Toggle activates open route only mode; 4. Toggle visual state confirms mode activation; 5. Map display updates to show filtered content; 6. Only selected job route remains visible on map; 7. All other vehicle paths are hidden while preserving route clarity
